{
  "texts": [
    "It is also known as a guided writing activity because learners become independent step by step.",
    "The product approach suggests that the learners brainstorm, discuss, elaborate, and finalize their ideas in a refined form.",
    "On the other hand, the process approach encourages the learners to brainstorm cooperatively, form several drafts, and edit based on the feedback before the submission, so the writing process is a cycle of exchanging ideas and eliminating the weak points before the submission (Menggo and Gunas, 2022; Strobel and Van Barneveld, 2009).",
    "It can be argued that the teacher-centered mode has been reduced to leave room for the student-centered method in the process approach.",
    "The latest trend in teaching writing more effectively is the genre approach which is designed to enhance students' writing competence through different genres, such as reports, biographies, essays, and theses."
  ]
}